        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(models-config): unify auth-profile fingerprint cache + targetProvider short-circuit",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nSupersedes #73260 and #73261 with one reconciled implementation. The two are **complementary, not redundant** — both avoid the expensive `resolveImplicitProviders` path (plugin discovery fan-out + live provider-catalog fetches), layered in `ensureOpenClawModelsJson` as: in-process whole-input **fingerprint cache** (warm-process memoizer) → provider-scoped **structural short-circuit** (cold-start / cross-provider-change skip) → full plan.\n\nReconciled here:\n\n- **#73260** — content-hash auth-profile fingerprint + `models.json` drift detection. Warm-process whole-input memoizer; OAuth token rotation no longer busts the cache.\n- **#73261** — provider-scoped `targetProvider` structural short-circuit with disk-vs-config validation. Skips discovery on cold start / gateway restart, or when an *unrelated* provider changed.\n\nPlus a correctness fix shared by both PRs, and carried refinements:\n\n- **Fingerprint the canonical SQLite auth store** (`openclaw-agent.sqlite`, via the warm pooled handle) instead of the legacy `auth-profiles.json` file. Both prior PRs hashed the legacy JSON, which reads `absent` for every agent already migrated to SQLite — so real credential changes never invalidated the implicit-provider-discovery cache. Reading the canonical store fixes that, removes the symlink / oversize-file attack surface (it's a DB read, not a file read), and aligns with the \"SQLite only / no legacy runtime readers\" storage policy. Volatile OAuth session fields are still stripped before hashing, so token rotation stays cache-stable.\n- **Per-type token-expiry volatile fields** — `type:\"token\"` profiles keep `expires*` in the hash so an expired static token invalidates the cache, while OAuth session rotation does not.\n- **Plugin-catalog wiring** — merge generated plugin catalogs into the pre-plan parsed `models.json` and write them in the skip / noop / write paths.\n\nAll security hardenings from both PRs are preserved (fail-closed `uncacheable`, prototype-pollution guards, bounded compare depth, per-model transport refusal, validated-outcome TOCTOU close, scoped-cache isolation).\n\n## Review feedback (round 1 — Codex/Clawsweeper durable review)\n\nBoth blocking findings from the durable review (verdict: *needs changes + needs real behavior proof*, head `1621b52177`) are addressed in commit `e1524762ec`:\n\n- **[P1] Validate plugin catalog sidecars before warm cache returns** (`src/agents/models-config.ts:1501-1504`). The branch had moved drift detection to a content outcome on the cache entry but only captured root `models.json`, leaving the generated plugin catalog sidecars (`plugins/<plugin>/catalog.json`, written by the planner and consumed by `ModelRegistry.loadCustomModels`) unvalidated — a sidecar deleted/tampered after a warm entry was cached would still hit the cache and skip reconciliation (provider-routing integrity hole). Fixed by adding `readPluginCatalogsContentOutcome` (a `ContentHashOutcome` over the sorted `(relativePath, content-hash)` pairs of every generated sidecar), captured on the ready-cache entry across all write/skip/noop/short-circuit paths and re-checked on every warm hit (global + scoped) alongside `modelsJsonOutcome`. Strictly stronger than main's mtime fingerprint: hashes sidecar *contents* (catches mtime-preserving tamper) and folds the sidecar path set into the digest (catches add/delete). Fail-closed: an `uncacheable` sidecar never compares equal.\n\n- **[P2] Avoid creating the auth database for a fingerprint read** (`src/agents/models-config.ts:295`). `readAuthProfilesStableOutcome` routed through `openAuthProfileDatabase`, which `mkdir`s the agent dir, creates the schema, and registers the DB — a write side effect for a read-only cache-key computation. Fixed by calling `readPersistedAuthProfileStoreRaw(agentDir)` with no DB handle, taking the no-create / `{ readOnly: true }` path. No agent SQLite state is materialized to decide cache usability.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` → clean\n- `pnpm tsgo:core:test` → clean\n- `pnpm vitest run` (the 3 acceptance-criteria files: `models-config.fingerprint-cache.test.ts`, `models-config.write-serialization.test.ts`, `models-config.target-provider-short-circuit.test.ts`) → **112 passed**, including 4 new regression tests pinning sidecar drift + no-DB-create\n- `pnpm config:schema:check` → ok\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check` → ok\n- `pnpm oxlint` (touched files) → clean of new errors (2 pre-existing `no-promise-executor-return` lines are outside this diff)\n- `git diff --check` → clean\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nReal-runtime proof script `scripts/proof-90741-plugin-catalog-cache-validation.ts` drives the real `ensureOpenClawModelsJson` against a real on-disk agent directory, real generated plugin-catalog sidecars, the real `readyCache` populate/drift cycle, and the real no-create auth-store read. **No mocking of the seam under test**; only the network edge is avoided (static `apiKey`, no live provider catalog fetch).\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** A plugin-catalog sidecar deleted or tampered after a warm models-config cache entry was created still hit the cache and skipped reconciliation (provider-routing integrity hole, [P1]); separately, the read-only auth fingerprint computation created the agent SQLite DB as a write side effect ([P2]). After the fix, sidecar drift busts the warm cache and the rogue file is reconciled away, and the fingerprint read never materializes the auth DB.\n- **Real environment tested:** Real `ensureOpenClawModelsJson` runtime path driven against an on-disk temp agent directory with real generated plugin-catalog sidecars, the real `readyCache` populate/drift cycle, and the real no-create auth-store read. Topic worktree at head `e1524762ec`. No mocking of the seam under test; only the network edge is avoided (static apiKey, no live provider fetch).\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** `node --import tsx scripts/proof-90741-plugin-catalog-cache-validation.ts` (equivalently `pnpm tsx scripts/proof-90741-plugin-catalog-cache-validation.ts`), run from the topic worktree.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Captured terminal output (stdout) from the live run of the proof against the real cache code path:\n\n```\n[1/3] sidecar-drift-busts-cache-and-reconciles\n    rogue sidecar present after re-plan: false\n    ok\n[2/3] fingerprint-read-does-not-create-agent-db\n    auth DB created: false, -wal: false, -shm: false\n    ok\n[3/3] stable-no-sidecar-still-hits\n    models.json mtimeMs cold=1780794326032.3853 warm=1780794326032.3853 ino cold=3879005 warm=3879005\n    ok\n\nAll runtime assertions passed.\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** All three runtime assertions passed (process exit 0). Scenario 1 — the rogue sidecar is absent after re-plan (`rogue sidecar present after re-plan: false`): the warm cache correctly missed on sidecar drift and `removeStalePluginCatalogs` reconciled the tampered file away. Scenario 2 — no `openclaw-agent.sqlite` / `-wal` / `-shm` was created by the fingerprint read (`auth DB created: false, -wal: false, -shm: false`): the read-only cache-key computation no longer has a write side effect. Scenario 3 — steady-state no-sidecar inputs still hit the cache (identical `models.json` inode and mtime cold vs warm), confirming no perf regression.\n- **What was not tested:** A fully live multi-provider gateway boot is not exercised; the cache populate/drift/reconcile and no-create auth-read paths are driven end-to-end against real on-disk state by the proof script above. Unit coverage (`models-config.fingerprint-cache.test.ts` + 3 acceptance files, 112 passed) is supplemental.",
